data-triple-N3.o: "Doctor of Medicine (MD, from the Latin Medicinae Doctor meaning "Teacher of Medicine") is a degree for physicians. In some countries it is a professional doctorate where training is entered after obtaining between 90 and 120 credit hours of university level work and in most cases after obtaining a Bachelors Degree. In other countries, such as India, the United Kingdom, Germany, and Sri Lanka, the M.D. is a research degree more similar to a Masters degree."@en
